# bootc/trust-keys/.gitignore
#
# ABSOLUTELY NO PRIVATE KEY MATERIAL IS TRACKED IN THIS REPO.
# The project MOK private key lives in CI secrets (GHCR / GitHub Actions
# secret store). Dev machines generate their own ephemeral keys here;
# neither the private nor the public key ever hits git.
#
# Tracked: this .gitignore, README.md (lifecycle docs), and any
# *.example / *.template sample files that show FORMAT only.
#
# Ignored: everything that could be a real key.

# Private keys — PEM, DER, PKCS#8, OpenSSH, sshd, GPG
*.pem
*.key
*.priv
*.pkcs8
*.pkcs12
*.p12
*.pfx

# DER certs get split into pub/priv; ignore all .der except *.example.der
*.der
!*.example.der

# sign-file / module signing intermediates
*.x509
signing_key.*
module_signing_key.*

# sbctl / shim MOK artifacts
mok.*
MOK.*
*.der.priv

# systemd-cryptenroll TPM policy artifacts that reference keys
*.pcrlock
*.pcrlock.sig

# scratch output from CI build runs
dist/
build/
out/
tmp/
*.asc
*.gpg

# But DO keep:
!README.md
!.gitignore
!*.example
!*.template
